Admission of government-sponsored students to pivate universities will enable more people to acquire higher education, Gretsa University chancellor Dr Kibathi Mbugua has said. He said said the institution admitted 220 government students this year. Mbugua was speaking during the university&rsquo;s seventh graduation ceremony in Thika town on Wednesday.&ldquo;This year 10,000 students joined private universities, while public universities took 74,000. If this trend continues, we are sure to train many more young people, increasing our competitiveness,&rdquo; he said.Mombasa Governor Hassan Joho was among the graduands, although he was absent.Mbugua said the university has put in place measures to ensure every student, regardless of their position, they meet all requirements before graduating. He said Joho has been a distance learning student since 2014.